  "response": "Here are some steps to start learning French:\n\n1. Learn basic pronunciation\n- Study French alphabet and sounds\n- Practice pronunciation with online resources\n\n2. Build a basic vocabulary\n- Start with common words and phrases\n- Use language learning apps like Duolingo or Babbel\n- Get a beginner's French dictionary\n\n3. Use learning resources\n- YouTube tutorials\n- Language learning websites\n- Podcasts\n- French textbooks\n- Language exchange apps\n\n4. Practice listening skills\n- Watch French movies with subtitles\n- Listen to French music\n- Watch French YouTube channels\n- Use language learning podcasts\n\n5. Take structured lessons\n- Online courses\n- Local language classes\n- Private tutoring\n- Language learning apps with structured curriculum\n\n6. Immerse yourself\n- Change device language settings to French\n- Follow French social media accounts\n- Label household items in French\n- Try to think in French\n\n7. Set realistic goals\n- Start with basic conversation skills\n- Practice consistently\n- Be patient with yourself\n\n8. Consider additional practice methods\n- Flashcards\n- Conversation groups\n- Language exchange partners online\n\nRemember, consistency is key in language learning.",
